nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: L-Proline\nOVERALL STRATEGY: A comprehensive prebiotic synthesis network for L-Proline integrating four experimentally validated routes: (1) the glutamate\u2192GSA\u2192P5C reductive cascade via multiple \u03b1KG sources and amination mechanisms, (2) the Patel-Sutherland cyanosulfidic photochemistry with proper Cu(I)/Cu(II) photoredox intermediates, (3) an alternative succinaldehyde\u2192P5C bypass that avoids the problematic \u03b3-carboxyl reduction, and (4) HCN polymer hydrolysis. Five hub molecules (HCN, pyruvate, \u03b1-ketoglutarate, glutamate, P5C) create dense convergence. Chirality amplification addresses the L-selection problem via crystal-solution eutectic enrichment and CPL-assisted UV photolysis. Environmental flow proceeds primarily Hydrothermal (carbon fixation) \u2192 Surface (condensation, photochemistry) \u2192 Biochemical (assembly, amplification), with cross-environment feedback.\n\nMOLECULES (22 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen gas) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: H2S (hydrogen sulfide) [starting]\n  - mol_005: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: CH3COCOO- (pyruvate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_007: C2HO3- (glyoxylate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C5H4O5 (alpha-ketoglutarate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C5H9NO4 (glutamic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C5H9NO3 (glutamic-gamma-semialdehyde (GSA)) [intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C5H7NO2 (delta-1-pyrroline-5-carboxylic acid (P5C)) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C5H9NO2 (DL-proline (racemic)) [intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C5H9NO2 (L-proline) [target]\n  - mol_014: CH3NO (formamide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C4H5NOS (4-C cyanohydrin-thiol (cyanosulfidic intermediate)) [intermediate]\n  - mol_016: C4H5NOS (gamma-butyrothiolactam) [inte